83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
A-Engrossed
House Bill 4160
Ordered by the House February 17
Including House Amendments dated February 17
Sponsored by COMMITTEE ON RULES (at the request of Representative Dwayne Yunker)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability standards.
Digest: Requires schools to have a plan for a cardiac emergency, which must include AEDs.
(Flesch Readability Score: 65.7).
Directs schools to have a cardiac emergency response plan as part of the procedures for re-
sponding to medical emergencies. Prescribes the requirements of a cardiac emergency response
plan, including requirements related to automated external defibrillators.
Takes effect July 1, [2026] 2027.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to procedures for medical emergencies in schools; creating new provisions; amending ORS
3 339.345 and 339.405; and prescribing an effective date.
4 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
5 SECTION 1. ORS 339.405 is amended to read:
6 339.405. (1) As used in this section:
7 (a) “Evacuate” means a procedure used when students and staff need to move from one location
8 to another.
9 (b) “Hold” means a procedure used to keep students and staff in classrooms while a disruption
10 or minor emergency is resolved.
11 (c) “Lockdown” means a procedure used when a threat or hazard is inside the building.
12 (d) “Secure” means a procedure used when a threat or hazard is outside the building.
13 (e) “Shelter in place” is a procedure used to respond to and take protective actions based on a
14 threat or hazard that may include an earthquake, tsunami or other natural or environmental hazard.
15 (2) Each school district must maintain a comprehensive safety program for all students and staff.
16 The program must include procedures for:
17 (a) Responding to emergency situations that address an immediate threat to safety, including an
18 evacuation, a hold, a lockdown, a secure and a shelter in place;
19 (b) Providing communicable disease management;
20 (c) Responding to medical emergencies, including a cardiac emergency response plan that
21 complies with ORS 339.345; and
22 (d) Providing instruction as described in ORS 339.408.
23 (3) The State Board of Education may adopt rules related to a program required under this
24 section.
25 SECTION 2. ORS 339.345 is amended to read:
26 339.345. [Each school campus in a school district, private school campus and public charter school
NOTE: Matter in boldfaced type in an amended section is new; matter [italic and bracketed] is existing law to be omitted.
New sections are in boldfaced type.
LC 125

A-Eng. HB 4160
1 campus shall have on the premises at least one automated external defibrillator.] Every kindergarten
2 through grade 12 public or private school is required to have a plan for cardiac emergency
3 responses. The plan must:
4 (1) To the greatest extent practicable, align with core elements established by a national
5 organization focused on emergency cardiovascular care.
6 (2) Include the provision of at least one automated external defibrillator at the school.
7 (3) Provide for the placement of automated external defibrillators in a manner that:
8 (a) To the greatest extent practicable, is in accordance with guidelines established by a
9 national organization focused on emergency cardiovascular care; and
10 (b) Is in locations that are clearly identified, unlocked and accessible when:
11 (A) Students are at school; and
12 (B) Students are at athletic practices or competitions at the school.
13 (4) Establish a procedure for the sharing of the locations of automated external
14 defibrillators at the school with local emergency medical services providers.
15 (5) Require the maintenance and testing of automated external defibrillators at the
16 school as provided by the manufacturer’s guidelines.
17 (6) Require every coach, as defined in ORS 336.485, and other appropriate staff, as de-
18 termined by the school, to be trained in cardiopulmonary resuscitation and the use of auto-
19 mated external defibrillators.
20 (7) Provide for an annual review of the plan and review of whether the school is in
21 compliance with the plan.
22 SECTION 3. The amendments to ORS 339.345 and 339.405 by sections 1 and 2 of this 2026
23 Act first apply to the 2027-2028 school year.
24 SECTION 4. This 2026 Act takes effect on July 1, 2027.
